"Get me Canada, get me the British, get me the Russians, get me the Chinese, get me the French, get me the Germans, get me the Japanese, anyone! Now!" She screamed toward her aides.

The phones rang and rang but no one answered. The only way they were getting the news is with a very old CRT TV that still receives signal from old TV waves. Still operating on those old TV waves, the South American country of Columbia was the one that gave intel to the United States about the non-isolation. 10 hours shortly after the news, the TV signal went dark.

Still operating on those old TV waves, the South American country of Columbia was the one that gave intel to the United States about the non-isolation. 10 hours shortly after the news, the TV signal went dark.

The newly elected United States President, Roberta Lincoln, is determined to find out what happened to the rest of the world. She was furious. "Get me Canada, get me the British, get me the Russians, get me the Chinese, get me the French, get me the Germans, get me the Japanese, anyone! Now!" She screamed toward her aides.

The phones rang and rang but no one answered. The only way they were getting the news is with a very old CRT TV that still receives signal from old TV waves. Still operating on those old TV waves, the South American country of Columbia was the one that gave intel to the United States about the non-isolation. 10 hours shortly after the news, the TV signal went dark.

"Get me Canada, get me the British, get me the Russians, get me the Chinese, get me the French, get me the Germans, get me the Japanese, anyone! Now!" She screamed toward her aides.

The phones rang and rang but no one answered. The only way they were getting the news is with a very old CRT TV that still receives signal from old TV waves. Still operating on those old TV waves, the South American country of Columbia was the one that gave intel to the United States about the non-isolation. 10 hours shortly after the news, the TV signal went dark.

"We have a problem," said the President. Her aides were quick to find a solution. Was it a coordinated plan to isolate the United States? Was it a terrorist plot? Or was it just a simple misunderstanding.

The phones rang and rang but no one answered. The only way they were getting the news is with a very old CRT TV that still receives signal from old TV waves. Still operating on those old TV waves, a mysterious signal was the one that gave intel to the United States about the non-isolation. 10 hours shortly after the news, the TV signal went dark.

"We have a problem," said the President. Her aides were quick to find a solution. Was it a coordinated plan to isolate the United States? Was it a terrorist plot? Or was it just a simple misunderstanding. 

The aides reported back to the president with their report. Their reactivated satellites that were dormant for 50 years revealed no movement nor any other human activity visible in the other parts of the world.

"They just left, Ms. President," said one of the aides. "We've tracked a spaceship heading towards Mars. The last people on earth left 10 hours ago."
